-- FACTBOX: Ten worst months for the Dow and S&P 500
-- 
-- Fri Oct 31, 2008 5:48pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/31/us-usa-stocks-monthly-idUSTRE49U7JC20081031

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - October 2008 was a month to forget for global stocks, with the Dow Jones industrial average and the S&P 500 mirroring lousy performances by other indexes around the world. 

 The S&P 500 fell 16.83 percent in October, its ninth-biggest monthly percentage decline ever. The Dow dropped 14.06 percent in October -- its 17th-worst month ever. Here is a list of the 10 worst months on record for both indexes, in terms of percentage declines. S&P 500 Month/year             Pct decline      Points decline September 1931         -29.94             -4.15 March 1938                 -25.04             -2.84 May 1940                     -23.95             -2.92 May 1932                    -23.33             -1.36 October 1987             -21.76            -70.04 April 1932                   -20.25             -1.48 October 1929             -19.93             -6.01 February 1933            -18.44             -1.28 October 2008              -16.83           -195.99 June 1930                   -16.46             -4.03